==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Flax-plant
<hw>Flax"-plant`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<def>A plant in new Zealand (<spn>Phormium tenax</spn>), allied to the
lilies and aloes. The leaves are two inches wide and several feet long,
and furnish a fiber which is used for making ropes, mats, and coarse
cloth.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Flaxseed</ent>⟦br⟧
